The paper proposes a computational model for shape, illumination, and albedo inference in a pulsed time-of-flight (TOF) camera. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for depth imaging and graphics (GR) techniques for illumination and albedo inference. The use of non-parametric regression trees suggests machine learning (LG) techniques are also involved. The paper also addresses optimal exposure design in pulsed TOF systems, which suggests robotics (RO) techniques may be involved. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.RO, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
